      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury: 4.18%. WMB operates much like a utility. With stable cash flows immune to commodity price swings, an 8.5% discount rate provides an adequate margin over the risk-free rate for infrastructure equity.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Natural gas will be critical for power generation for decades, especially with surging AI data center electricity demand. However, a 2.5% terminal growth rate assumes volume growth eventually flattens long-term due to renewables penetration.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

